 Forces & Society]] |location=[[Piscataway, NJ]] |volume=15 |issue=4 |pages=489\u2013505 |doi=10.1177/0095327X8901500402 |oclc=49621350 |url=https://zenodo.org/record/1235548 }}\n* {{Cite news |last=Petraeus |first=David H. |last2=Brennan |first2=Robert A. |publication-date=January\u2013February 1997 |year=1997 |title=Walk and Shoot Training |periodical=Infantry Magazine |publication-place=Ft. Benning, GA |publisher=U.S. Army Infantry School |volume=87 |issue=1 |pages=36\u201340 |url=https://www.benning.army.mil/magazine/1997/1997_1/index.htm |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304001309/https://www.benning.army.mil/magazine/1997/1997_1/index.htm |url-status=dead |archive-date=March 4, 2016 |accessdate=August 10, 2011}}<ref>\"Walk and Shoot Training\" File:Petraeus Brennan Walk and Shoot.pdf</ref>\n* {{Cite news |last=Petraeus |first=David H. |last2=Carr |first2=Damian P. |last3=Abercrombie |first3=John C. |publication-date=May\u2013June 1997 |year=1997 |title=Why We Need FISTs\u2014Never Send a Man When You Can Send a Bullet |periodical=Field Artillery |publication-place=[[Fort Sill, OK]] |publisher=[[United States Army Field Artillery School|US Army Field Artillery School]] |volume=1997 |issue=3 |pages=3\u20135 |url=http://sill-www.army.mil/FAMAG/1997/MAY_JUN_1997/MAY_JUN_1997_PAGES_3_5.pdf |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927130233/http://sill-www.army.mil/FAMAG/1997/MAY_JUN_1997/MAY_JUN_1997_PAGES_3_5.pdf |url-status=dead |archive-date=September 27, 2007 |format=PDF|issn=0899-2525 |id=HQDA PB6-97-3, USPS 309-010, [[PURL]], SuDoc No. D 101.77/2: 1997/3 |oclc=16516511 |accessdate=August 26, 2007}},\n* {{cite web|title=Lessons of the Iraq War and Its Aftermath|url=http://www.ciaonet.org/pbei/winep/policy_2004/2004_855/2004_855.html|publisher=Washington Institute for Near East Policy|year=2004}}{{Dead link|date=January 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n* (2006) \"Learning Counterinsurgency: Observations from Soldiering in Ira